                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12538935" author="karlpauls" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2007 22:24:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue boils done to the TldLocationCache assuming that it can just open a connection to any URL in a given URLClassloader without catching exceptions. I would argue that this is a bug in Tomcat.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, I don&apos;t see any problem (other then introducing one extra class) with just returning a URLConnection that will throw an IOException on connect() v.s. throwing an IOException directly. This change is in as of revision 590492. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please test whether this makes your problem go away and if so close this issue. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12539091" author="martijnh" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2007 14:52:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your quick response, your patch resolves our problem. I agree that this could best be characterized as a bug in Tomcat and it is great that you nevertheless provided this solution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
